# CODEOWNERS
# Each line is a file pattern followed by one or more owners.
# Order matters: later patterns override earlier ones.
# See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default owner for everything
*                               @projectamazonph

# Documentation requires a docs-savvy reviewer
/docs/                          @projectamazonph
*.md                            @projectamazonph

# Architecture-critical: domain and ports changes need explicit review
/src/domain/                    @projectamazonph
/src/ports/                     @projectamazonph

# Use cases orchestrate; less surface for breakage but still architecture-critical
/src/usecases/                  @projectamazonph

# Infrastructure adapters (third-party SDKs, schemas) — explicit review
/prisma/                        @projectamazonph
/src/infra/                     @projectamazonph

# Composition root wires the dependency graph — single owner
/src/composition/               @projectamazonph

# CI / infra
/.github/                       @projectamazonph
/package.json                   @projectamazonph
/pnpm-lock.yaml                 @projectamazonph

# Stories and sprint plans — sprint cadence review
/docs/sprint-*/                 @projectamazonph
/docs/stories/                  @projectamazonph
/docs/sprint-plan.md            @projectamazonph
/docs/decisions.md              @projectamazonph
